President Obama has announced his intent to nominate J. Mark McWatters for the position of Member, Board of Directors of the Export-Import Bank of the United States. McWatters is currently a Member of the National Credit Union Administration Board and has previously served as the Director of Graduate Programs and an adjunct professor at the Southern Methodist University Dedman School of Law. He has also served on various boards and committees, including the Texas Department of Housing and Community Affairs and the Advisory Committee of the Texas Emerging Technology Fund. McWatters has a diverse background in law and finance, having worked as a tax and corporate counsel, as well as a partner in several law firms. He holds multiple degrees, including a B.B.A., M.B.A., J.D., and two L.L.M. degrees.